# Commit and Push Workflow

- When the user asks to commit, create a semantic commit message from the actual diff and run `git commit`.
- Use conventional commit format:
  - `type(scope): TICKET summary` when a ticket (e.g. `PMP-123`, `BB-456`) can be inferred from branch name.
  - `type(scope): summary` when no ticket is present in the branch name.
- Commit message body should summarize intent per changed file in concise, factual lines.
- Do not run `git push` as part of commit flow.
- Only run `git push` when the user explicitly asks for push in a separate step.
